# Dark-Minimalist

# Separation for the items in the titlebar (buttons, window title)
padding.width: 5
padding.height: 7

## Titlebar
window.active.title.bg: flat
window.active.title.bg.color: #1c1b22
window.inactive.title.bg: flat
window.inactive.title.bg.color: #1c1b22
window.*.title.separator.color: #1c1b22  

## Titlebar Text
window.label.text.justify: center
window.active.label.bg: parentrelative
window.active.label.text.color: #1c1b22
window.inactive.label.bg: parentrelative
window.inactive.label.text.color: #1c1b22

## Borders  (The title bar and the window have independent borders)
border.width: 2
window.active.border.color: #ababab
window.inactive.border.color: #ababab

## Handle   (Bottom border used to increase the size of the window vertically. The value set is independent of the border value.)
window.handle.width: 0
window.active.handle.bg: flat
window.active.handle.bg.color: #1c1b22
window.inactive.handle.bg: flat
window.inactive.handle.bg.color: #1c1b22

## Client   (Spaces on the sides of the window. The value set is independent of the border value.)
window.client.padding.width: 0
window.client.padding.height: 0
window.active.client.color:  #1c1b22
window.inactive.client.color:  #1c1b22

## Grip     (Left and righ border used to increase the size of the window horizontally. the value set is independent of the border value.)
window.active.grip.bg: flat
window.active.grip.bg.color: #1c1b22
window.inactive.grip.bg: flat
window.inactive.grip.bg.color: #1c1b22

